  "texts": [
    "5 Some health systems have recently hired prompt engineers to adapt general-purpose LLMs for medical applications, and to design, test, and evaluate various prompts.",
    "Future research could systematically examine patterns in the prompts that users adopt to obtain desired answers, and help develop guidelines for the effective use of prompt engineering in health care.",
    "Because LLMs are trained on huge quantities of internet data, they are susceptible to outside attacks, creating risks for model security and privacy.",
    "Researchers have demonstrated the ease and inexpensiveness with which attackers can inject false or misleading information into a model's training data-sometimes called \"data poisoning.\"",
    "6 This can occur when even a small fraction (e.g., 0.1%) of instances in a dataset is altered."
  ],
